---
const facts = [
  { label: 'Based in',  value: 'Jakarta, Indonesia' },
  { label: 'Studying',  value: 'CS at Fasilkom UI' },
  { label: 'Languages', value: 'Bahasa Indonesia, English' },
  { label: 'Currently', value: 'PPL: SIAsisten Reborn' },
];
---

<section id="about" class="py-28 px-6 reveal">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <h3 class="section-h">
      <span class="step">01.</span>About me
    </h3>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-5 gap-10 items-start">
      <div class="md:col-span-3 space-y-4 leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--color-text-muted);">
        <p>
          Started CS at Universitas Indonesia in 2023. By the third semester
          I'd shipped enough Django apps, Spring services, and ML notebooks
          to figure out which parts of the stack I keep coming back to:
          mostly backends and ML pipelines.
        </p>
        <p>
          Most of my time these days goes to{' '}
          <span class="text-accent">SIAsisten Reborn</span>. My team is
          rebuilding Fasilkom UI's teaching-assistant management system for
          2026 in our PPL course, replacing one that's been in production for
          over a decade. Django REST backend, React Router 7 frontend, with the
          production sundries: CAS SSO, structured logging, Prometheus, GitLab
          CI fronted by SonarQube.
        </p>
        <p>
          The rest goes to data-science competitions with a small crew of
          friends. Finalist twice (AIRNOLOGY DataQuest 2024, SPARK Telkomsel
          2025) and 3rd at Datathon RISTEK 2024. Lately the work has been more
          NLP and CV than tabular.
        </p>
        <p>
          When I'm not doing either of those, I'm tinkering with Godot or
          reading too much about ML systems.
        </p>
      </div>

      <aside
        class="md:col-span-2 rounded-lg p-6"
        style="background: color-mix(in oklch, var(--color-surface) 60%, transparent); border: 1px solid var(--color-border);"
      >
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-sm">
          {facts.map((f) => (
            <li class="grid grid-cols-[6.5rem_1fr] gap-2">
              <span style="color: var(--color-text-dim);">{f.label}</span>
              <span style="color: var(--color-text);">{f.value}</span>
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
